===Etymology===
Name taken from the [[Falkland Sound]], which were named for {{w|Viscount Falkland}} by [[w:John Strong (mariner)|John Strong]], who landed on the islands in 1690.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|head=the Falkland Islands}} {{g|p}}

# Overseas territory of the [[United Kingdom]], located in the South [[Atlantic]]. Official name: Falkland Islands. Argentina contests the British sovereignty in the islands.

